# Release and Homebrew

Applies when editing files under `scripts/`. For **`Casks/`**, **`project.yml`** (version fields), or **`.github/workflows/`**, follow the same conventions (see [heartbit-core](heartbit-core.mdc) and the skill below).

- **Canonical build:** [`scripts/heartbit-build.sh`](scripts/heartbit-build.sh) — `dev` (Debug + open app) or `release` (zip + SHA-256). Root [`build.sh`](build.sh) forwards to the same script.
- **Release zip name:** `Release/HeartBit-v<version>.zip` where `<version>` is `CFBundleShortVersionString` in [`project.yml`](project.yml) (must include the **`v`** prefix). GitHub asset URL pattern matches [`Casks/heartbit.rb`](Casks/heartbit.rb).
- **Do not** reintroduce scripts that run `xcodebuild` on `HeartBit.xcodeproj` **without** running XcodeGen first, or that emit `HeartBit-1.2.3.zip` (missing `v`).
- **Publish:** [`scripts/publish_release.sh`](scripts/publish_release.sh) bumps `project.yml`, updates the cask, commits, tags `v*`, pushes, and uses `gh release create`. Prefer `--dry-run` first. Full checklist: [`.cursor/skills/heartbit-release/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/heartbit-release/SKILL.md).
- **Checks:** After cask edits, `brew audit --cask --strict heartbit` with the repo tapped locally is the expected gate.
